9 Sec. 4. 22 MRSA §264, sub-§5, ¶H, as enacted by PL 2021, c. 398, Pt. MMMM,
10 §2, is amended by amending subparagraph (1) to read:
11 (1) Name, age, sex, race or ethnicity, guardianship status and type of disability or
12 condition of the adult receiving services who is deceased;
13 SUMMARY
1144 Under current law, the Aging and Disability Mortality Review Panel reviews deaths of
1155 and serious injuries to adults receiving services in home-based and community-based
1166 services programs, including participants in those programs who are subject to public
1177 guardianship. This bill expands the charge of the panel to review all deaths of and serious
1188 injuries to adults subject to public guardianship, whether or not they are enrolled in home-
1199 based and community-based services programs. It also amends the membership of the
2200 panel.
